title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1995-03-17
description:
Set 1

Here Comes Sunshine, Wang Dang Doodle, Peggy-O, Queen Jane Approximately, Lazy River Road, Eternity*, Loose Lucy (55 mins)

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samba In The Rain-> Truckin'-> New Speedway Boogie-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> All Along The Watchtower-> Standing On the Moon-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Lucy In The Sky With Diamonds (85 mins)

* Weir on acoustic; Several takes of Unbroken Chain were done for soundcheck/rehearsal.

reviews.review_text:
Say What You Want About 1995 Dead...... .....but this show completely rocks!  The band gets off to a rough start with some ragged harmonies on "Here Comes Sunshine," but the audience seems to mind not a bit.  By the time they get to "Peggy-O" the band seems to have decided that tonight is going to be a slow burn, and they deliver a fantastic version of the song followed by a sweet "Queen Jane."  The second set really gets things going, and for my money, this may be one of the best Disc 3's of the year -- it's certainly in the Top 5.  Standing > Sugar Mags > Lucy in the Sky isn't a song combo you're going to see a lot, but boy does it work.  

Soundwise, things are lacking just a bit.  There's just a bit too much echo, and I'm left oscillating between calling this a "B+" or an "A-".  Still, The Spectrum was one of the best places to see a concert in the US, and you can really hear the room on this tape.  Not the most circulated source from this date, but definitely worth your time to check out. '95 rules!
